text:
Hi,

Tomcat 4.0-b5 over Windows2000 might have the following error. When using a 
servlet to connect via RMI with a remote object and pass a CUSTOM serializable 
object as a parameter, an exception is thrown, when the server tries to 
unmarshal the object.

Ex: 

1) Create a serializale CUSTOM class:

public class Employee implements java.io.Serializable {

private String name;

public Employee(String name) {

this.name = name;

}

public String toString() {

return name;

}

}

2) Create a server that uses RMI to register a remote object that has a unique 
method "showName(Employee) that receives an Employee object argument and 
returns "toString()".

3) Create a servlet that lookup the remote object and call the remote 
method "showName" with a local crated Employee object.

4) This example will produce an exception with the following text:

java.rmi.ServerException: RemoteException occurred in server thread; nested 
exception is:
java.rmi.UnmarshalException: error unmarshalling arguments; nested exception 
is:       java.net.MalformedURLException: unknown protocol: jndi  at ...
